1. An expense has an amount and a flag recording whether it was approved.
2. A batch is a collection of expenses.
3. A claim has an amount and a flag recording whether it was approved.
4. Build one audit line for a batch: start with the header "audit:" and append each expense's amount in turn.
5. The total of a batch is the sum of every expense's amount.
6. The flagged count of a batch is how many of its expenses exceed the review threshold of 500.
7. A batch is fully approved when every expense in it is approved; report 1 when it is, 0 otherwise.
8. Check a claim: when it is approved, accept its amount if the amount is at most 1000, otherwise reject it as over the limit; when it is not approved, reject it as not approved.
9. Screen a claim by delegating to the claim check, then propagate the outcome: on success return the accepted amount, on failure return the rejection reason.
10. Discount a claim by 5% when the claim check accepts it; when the check rejects the claim, report -1.
